Dear friends,

=C7=E1=CA=D1=CC=E3=C9 =C7=E1=DA=D1=C8=ED=C9 =C3=CF=E4=C7=E5

Warm greetings to all of you! I hope this finds you well and that the year =
of 2026 has begun in a good way for you all!

I am writing today with an overall update on how we hope to set a direction=
 for the future work of the Maghreb Network. It is slightly longer e-mail s=
o I hope that you will find time to read it all.

As I have mentioned many times before, we have gone through a lot of intern=
al changes at SweFOR and we have had a long wait to understand what our ove=
rall funding partnerships will look like going forward. We now, finally, ha=
ve that clarity and we have a platform on which we can build our work for t=
he next three years!

It has been somewhat of a frustrating wait and for all the patience that yo=
u have all showed in different ways =96 thank you! During this time, so muc=
h of our shared work has also developed in lots of interesting and good way=
s, and today we have a range of very interesting projects and collaboration=
s that are running well thanks to the shared relationships and foundations =
we have in our network. It is a true pleasure to be in touch with many of y=
ou connected to these projects and collaborations, and also to be in touch =
when there are significant updates and life events. Many things have happen=
ed in the last years =96 people have got new jobs, started new studies, got=
 married, celebrated successes, and dealt with challenges and losses. In th=
is way, our network is working very well and the foundation of our relation=
ships is strong!

At the same time, what is also true is that we still need to determine the =
best way forward for our collective work in this network and how this can s=
erve us in the best possible way. Looking back to last year, we tried diffe=
rent versions of online meetings as we were waiting for the overall clarity=
 on our partnership situation. I think it is fair to say that these online =
meetings have had their ups and downs in terms of how useful they have felt=
. And when I last sent one of these longer updates to all of you with some =
questions about future desires for the online meetings, there were very few=
 responses.

This leads us to where we go from here. We still have a strong foundation i=
n our network, we have lots of interesting work taking place and we have th=
e possibility to make clear plans for the future. What we need to figure ou=
t and understand is how to do our shared work in a way that best serves the=
 interests and needs of all network members going forward.

Our process for figuring this out will be to contact you all individually t=
o schedule calls which each of you. In these calls, what we hope to underst=
and is:

1) Are you still interested in being part of the Maghreb network?
2) What work, initiatives, etc., that you are currently involved in can be =
supported by the network?
3) What is the best format for this support going forward?

We will contact all of you =96 regardless of how much or little we have bee=
n in touch in this last year =96 and hope to get a chance to speak to every=
one. It will be very important in order to determine our direction going fo=
rward.

We will begin this process in the coming days and hope to have it all final=
ized by the end of Ramadan, and then be able to return to everyone with a c=
lear set of priorities and a clear future direction for our shared work in =
this network.

We look forward to speaking to you all in the coming weeks! Until then, wis=
hing you all the very best.

On behalf of the SweFOR team,
Erik



